tus Jukes agonizing about his role on the secret medical commission tasked with reassessing Riel’s sanity, which would determine if he could be executed. The Winter Count is a cautionary tale about moral responsibility. As Leman laments, our failure to be accountable human beings will surely haunt us: "Laudable pus / Political speeches / This water / brought too late / to a boil / Lance and forceps / rattling / their pot"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359639940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773596399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773596399/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles